###########################################################################
#  text_subscript_superscript - chained @Sub / @Sup runs (the plain-text#
#  versions from bsf, not the @Eq versions).  Covers chemistry-style    #
#  formulae and ordinal markers, exercising baseline shift + font-size  #
#  reduction in both back ends.                                         #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
Plain-text scripts: water is H @Sub 2 O, glucose is C @Sub 6 H @Sub { 12 }
O @Sub 6, and Einstein's relation is E = mc @Sup 2.
@PP
Mixed runs: the 1 @Sup st, 2 @Sup nd, and 3 @Sup rd entries map to the
n @Sup th case in general, with bounds x @Sub 0, x @Sub 1, ..., x @Sub n.
@End @Text
